column1: # Middle Chinese to Mandarin syllable mapping (work in progress)
# The Middle Chinese syllables are transcribed using Baxter transcription.
# The Mandarin IPA transcription is intended to reflect the system of 洪武正韻譯訓. The following modern phonetic realization are not marked explicitly:
#  Merge of syllable codae -p -t -k to glottal stop [ʔ];
#  Omission of breathiness in breathy fricatives ʂʱ ʃʱ sʱ fʱ ɦ (resulting in merge with [ʂ] [ʃ] [s] [f] [h]~[x] respectively);
#  Palatalization and frictivization of /k/ /g/ /ŋ/ /ʔ/ /h/ /ɦ/ before /i/ or /y/;
